==English==
[[File:Yandex_Logo.svg|thumb|The logo of Yandex.]]
===Etymology===
The name initially stood for “Yet Another iNDEXer”. The Russian word {{m|ru|я}} corresponds to the English personal pronoun “I”, making ''Яndex'' a bilingual pun on {{m|en|index}}.
===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|en|/ˈjæn.dɛks/}}
===Proper noun===
{{en-proper noun}}
# A [[Russian]] Internet company which operates the largest [[search engine]] in Russia.
# {{lb|en|computing}} A [[search engine]] that popularized the company of the same name.
